591
00:20:08,860 --> 00:20:10,230
365.

592
00:20:18,460 --> 00:20:20,200
Did you fold all of these?

593
00:20:22,790 --> 00:20:23,630
There is more.

594
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:25,830
I also made a cake for you.

595
00:20:46,950 --> 00:20:48,750
I wanted to bring it out earlier,

596
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:52,010
but I was worried that they might laugh at it.

597
00:20:52,260 --> 00:20:53,860
It's not a fancy cream cake,

598
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:56,580
just a simple steamed egg cake that I made.

599
00:20:58,710 --> 00:21:00,240
The egg cake is my favorite.

600
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:06,110
It smells amazing.

601
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:13,030
Let me light a candle for you.

602
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:30,910
Make a wish.

603
00:21:46,850 --> 00:21:48,200
When is your birthday?

604
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:52,870
November 7.

605
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,860
Wait, that was yesterday.

606
00:21:58,630 --> 00:21:59,430
Why didn't you tell me

607
00:21:59,430 --> 00:22:01,490
that it was your birthday yesterday?

608
00:22:02,990 --> 00:22:04,250
Since my mom passed away,

609
00:22:04,250 --> 00:22:06,510
I haven't celebrated my birthday again.

610
00:22:06,890 --> 00:22:08,690
I don't even remember it myself.

611
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:09,950
Cut the cake first.

612
00:22:39,190 --> 00:22:41,270
Now, we're celebrating your birthday.

613
00:22:41,270 --> 00:22:42,200
Happy birthday.

614
00:22:44,790 --> 00:22:46,190
Let's be happy together.

615
00:22:47,510 --> 00:22:50,150
From now on, let's celebrate our birthdays

616
00:22:50,250 --> 00:22:51,130
on the same day.

617
00:22:52,190 --> 00:22:52,830
Okay.

618
00:22:53,430 --> 00:22:54,590
Make a wish. Come on.

619
00:22:59,990 --> 00:23:02,990
♫Happy birthday to you♫

620
00:23:03,190 --> 00:23:06,150
♫Happy birthday to you♫

621
00:23:06,430 --> 00:23:09,830
♫Happy birthday to you♫

622
00:23:10,030 --> 00:23:12,430
♫Happy birthday to you♫

623
00:23:15,450 --> 00:23:16,650
Here, birthday girl.

624
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:40,270
Pick up the phone.

625
00:23:46,750 --> 00:23:47,470
Hello?

626
00:23:49,030 --> 00:23:49,750
Uncle.

627
00:23:51,310 --> 00:23:52,150
My mom...

628
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:53,650
Say, I'm not at home.

629
00:23:54,590 --> 00:23:56,750
My mom is not at home.

630
00:23:57,710 --> 00:23:59,240
I don't know where she went.

631
00:23:59,670 --> 00:24:01,070
She hasn't come back yet.

632
00:24:02,470 --> 00:24:03,830
I've eaten.

633
00:24:05,550 --> 00:24:06,310
Okay.

634
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:07,390
Bye.

635
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:12,950
Mom.

636
00:24:19,150 --> 00:24:21,390
It's okay. Keep watching your show.

637
00:25:11,870 --> 00:25:13,550
The ideal of life

638
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:16,650
is to live an ideal life.

639
00:25:29,350 --> 00:25:31,950
You're like a light that illuminates my world.

640
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:41,230
Always keep your face toward the sun,

641
00:25:41,390 --> 00:25:43,990
so you won't see the shadows.

642
00:25:47,190 --> 00:25:49,240
Our scars

643
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:52,400
will become

644
00:25:52,950 --> 00:25:54,800
the source of our strength.

645
00:25:57,070 --> 00:25:59,150
Since we've chosen this path,

646
00:25:59,150 --> 00:26:01,950
just focus on forging ahead through wind and rain.

647
00:26:09,460 --> 00:26:10,530
Thank you.

648
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:27,240
You're welcome.

649
00:26:45,110 --> 00:26:45,870
Off you go.

650
00:27:06,820 --> 00:27:07,880
What are you doing?

651
00:27:08,750 --> 00:27:09,750
You startled me.

652
00:27:09,870 --> 00:27:10,800
I'm making soup.

653
00:27:12,070 --> 00:27:13,310
What's gotten into you?

654
00:27:13,310 --> 00:27:15,240
You're even making soup for us now?

655
00:27:15,630 --> 00:27:16,440
Let me see what kind of soup it is.

656
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,970
No, no, no, this soup is for someone else.

657
00:27:17,970 --> 00:27:19,570
I'll make you some tomorrow.

658
00:27:20,490 --> 00:27:21,550
What now this time?

659
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:23,790
Guess.

660
00:27:26,820 --> 00:27:27,790
Okay, class is over.

661
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:28,430
Stand up.

662
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:31,840
See you, sir.

663
00:27:31,870 --> 00:27:33,100
Goodbye, students.

664
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:45,640
Why didn't Qiang Xiaowa come to school today?

665
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:46,390
How would I know?

666
00:27:46,390 --> 00:27:47,920
He doesn't live in my house.

667
00:27:48,070 --> 00:27:49,670
What kind of attitude is that?

668
00:27:49,670 --> 00:27:51,180
What attitude should I have?

669
00:27:51,180 --> 00:27:52,050
He's a teenager.

670
00:27:52,050 --> 00:27:52,830
Nothing will happen to him.

671
00:27:52,830 --> 00:27:54,630
Why do you care so much about him?

672
00:27:54,750 --> 00:27:57,150
What's wrong with me caring about a friend?

673
00:28:08,150 --> 00:28:09,910
Ms. Han. Ms. Han?

674
00:28:10,990 --> 00:28:11,870
Someone is looking for you.

675
00:28:11,870 --> 00:28:13,270
He's at the gate with the guard.

676
00:28:13,270 --> 00:28:13,960
Who is it?

677
00:28:14,190 --> 00:28:14,920
I don't know.

678
00:28:15,870 --> 00:28:17,730
How about you come with me and see?

679
00:28:24,100 --> 00:28:30,590
♫Thinking about my childhood sweetheart...♫

680
00:28:31,490 --> 00:28:32,980
He's been looking for you for a while.

681
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:33,640
That's him.

682
00:28:35,870 --> 00:28:36,470
Look.

683
00:28:36,470 --> 00:28:38,320
I think I've seen him before.

684
00:28:37,750 --> 00:28:42,410
[Linqi Oilfield No. 2 High School]

685
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:39,220
Ms. Han!

686
00:28:40,220 --> 00:28:41,480
-That's him.
-Ms. Han.

687
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:43,850
You're Miaomiao's relative, right?

688
00:28:43,850 --> 00:28:45,570
Yes, Ms. Han.

689
00:28:45,900 --> 00:28:47,100
What brings you here?

690
00:28:47,420 --> 00:28:48,340
Nothing much.

691
00:28:48,470 --> 00:28:50,020
I was in the area

692
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:51,430
and thought I'd discuss

693
00:28:51,430 --> 00:28:52,910
Miaomiao's studies with you some more.

694
00:28:52,910 --> 00:28:53,630
But the security guy

695
00:28:53,630 --> 00:28:54,390
wouldn't let me in,

696
00:28:54,390 --> 00:28:55,550
thinking I was up to no good.

697
00:28:55,550 --> 00:28:57,230
No, Director Xiao just instructed

698
00:28:57,230 --> 00:28:58,870
that unauthorized visitors aren't allowed in.

699
00:28:58,870 --> 00:29:00,630
How am I an unauthorized visitor?

700
00:29:00,630 --> 00:29:02,120
Once a teacher, always a parent figure.

701
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,510
She's practically my niece's mother.

702
00:29:03,510 --> 00:29:04,670
We're family.

703
00:29:04,990 --> 00:29:05,590
If you have something,

704
00:29:05,590 --> 00:29:06,480
can't you talk here?

705
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:08,370
Do you really need to interrupt Ms. Han's class?

706
00:29:08,370 --> 00:29:10,510
Ms. Han, I didn't interrupt you, right?

707
00:29:10,510 --> 00:29:11,630
Besides, you see.

708
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:12,760
I'm already here.

709
00:29:15,790 --> 00:29:16,910
It's okay, Zhang.

710
00:29:17,070 --> 00:29:17,820
Let him in.

711
00:29:17,850 --> 00:29:19,080
Well, Director Xiao...

712
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:20,880
Alright. The leader has spoken.

713
00:29:29,910 --> 00:29:30,550
Remember my face.

714
00:29:30,550 --> 00:29:31,360
Don't stop me next time, got it?

715
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:32,400
We're family.

716
00:29:32,660 --> 00:29:33,660
-You...
-Ms. Han.

717
00:29:36,110 --> 00:29:36,950
Ms. Han.

718
00:29:45,310 --> 00:29:46,590
Miaomiao

719
00:29:46,780 --> 00:29:48,380
really didn't take after me.

720
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:50,760
She's, indeed, not very bright.

721
00:29:51,850 --> 00:29:53,780
Ms. Han, I know you've worked hard.

722
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:54,910
I made this soup

723
00:29:54,910 --> 00:29:56,390
this morning.

724
00:29:56,670 --> 00:29:57,670
A real old hen.

725
00:29:57,670 --> 00:29:58,460
I simmered it on low heat

726
00:29:58,460 --> 00:29:59,520
for several hours.

727
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:00,260
Try it.

728
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:04,030
But I have a class soon.

729
00:30:04,510 --> 00:30:05,590
If the other teachers see this,

730
00:30:05,590 --> 00:30:07,190
it may not reflect well on me.

731
00:30:07,490 --> 00:30:08,040
What if

732
00:30:08,070 --> 00:30:08,910
the director sees it...

733
00:30:08,910 --> 00:30:10,390
What's the big deal if she sees it?

734
00:30:10,390 --> 00:30:10,950
I...

735
00:30:11,140 --> 00:30:13,070
I've seen her sneaking dumplings before.

736
00:30:13,070 --> 00:30:13,670
You know?

737
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:15,770
So, she can eat dumplings,

738
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,200
but you can't drink soup?

739
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:18,430
I heard from the guard

740
00:30:18,430 --> 00:30:20,150
that someone unauthorized entered the school.

741
00:30:20,150 --> 00:30:20,670
Let's see who it is

742
00:30:20,670 --> 00:30:22,390
that has such little respect for campus rules.

743
00:30:22,390 --> 00:30:23,150
Director.

744
00:30:23,990 --> 00:30:25,320
Director, you're here.

745
00:30:25,710 --> 00:30:26,310
I came today

746
00:30:26,310 --> 00:30:27,470
as a representative of the parents

747
00:30:27,470 --> 00:30:29,580
to offer my support to you.

748
00:30:30,870 --> 00:30:32,150
I want to express

749
00:30:32,230 --> 00:30:33,390
my deep respect and admiration

750
00:30:33,390 --> 00:30:35,190
for you, the people's teachers.

751
00:30:36,190 --> 00:30:38,190
You are the gardeners of the nation.

752
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:40,070
If the youth are strong, the nation will be strong.

753
00:30:40,070 --> 00:30:41,190
And how do we ensure the youth are strong?

754
00:30:41,190 --> 00:30:42,460
It all depends on

755
00:30:42,460 --> 00:30:44,320
outstanding educators like you.

756
00:30:44,670 --> 00:30:45,870
What I'm doing here

757
00:30:45,870 --> 00:30:47,250
is really nothing.

758
00:30:47,550 --> 00:30:49,630
Please,

759
00:30:49,870 --> 00:30:52,730
have some of this chicken soup with my respect in it.

760
00:30:55,190 --> 00:30:56,070
Thank you.

761
00:30:56,070 --> 00:30:57,270
Thank you

762
00:30:57,320 --> 00:30:58,060
for your support and understanding

763
00:30:58,060 --> 00:30:59,140
of us educators.

764
00:30:59,350 --> 00:31:00,880
I'll drink it in your honor.

765
00:31:09,950 --> 00:31:11,350
This soup is pretty good.

766
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:11,950
Right?

767
00:31:12,290 --> 00:31:13,370
Have some more.

768
00:31:14,310 --> 00:31:15,870
You drink too. There's plenty.

769
00:31:15,870 --> 00:31:17,070
No, thanks.

770
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:18,770
My stomach's been a bit off.

771
00:31:18,990 --> 00:31:20,630
Our director loves soup.

772
00:31:20,710 --> 00:31:23,040
-Ms. Han
-What's wrong with your stomach?

773
00:31:23,150 --> 00:31:24,270
The director is here too?

774
00:31:24,270 --> 00:31:25,400
What are you eating?

775
00:31:25,470 --> 00:31:26,500
The parent brought some chicken soup.

776
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:27,430
Have some too.

777
00:31:27,980 --> 00:31:29,130
No, thanks.

778
00:31:30,260 --> 00:31:31,270
Who is this?

779
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:33,790
He is Cheng Miaomiao's homeroom teacher,

780
00:31:33,790 --> 00:31:34,630
Mr. Gao.

781
00:31:35,950 --> 00:31:36,790
Mr. Gao!

782
00:31:37,750 --> 00:31:38,990
I've heard a lot about you!

783
00:31:38,990 --> 00:31:40,270
Miaomiao keeps talking about you

784
00:31:40,270 --> 00:31:41,230
in front of me, really.

785
00:31:41,230 --> 00:31:42,280
I finally get to meet you today.

786
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:43,160
As they say,

787
00:31:43,590 --> 00:31:45,190
"Life is full of surprises."

788
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,590
This is my office.

789
00:31:47,590 --> 00:31:48,830
You can see me as long as you can come.

790
00:31:48,830 --> 00:31:50,030
Then I'll have to drop by more often.

791
00:31:50,030 --> 00:31:51,660
I love visiting your office

792
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:53,750
and soaking in the atmosphere of cultured folks.

793
00:31:53,750 --> 00:31:54,870
After that long chat

794
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:55,870
with Ms. Han last time,

795
00:31:55,870 --> 00:31:56,670
my mind

796
00:31:56,710 --> 00:31:58,150
has greatly improved.

797
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:00,360
My improvement

798
00:32:00,430 --> 00:32:01,950
has a lot to do with you.

799
00:32:02,070 --> 00:32:02,710
Right?

800
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:03,750
After all, I know.

801
00:32:03,980 --> 00:32:06,310
I heard that you two are seeing each other.

802
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:08,670
Seeing what?

803
00:32:10,080 --> 00:32:11,200
Are you two an item?

804
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:14,630
We're not like that.

805
00:32:17,270 --> 00:32:19,590
Then, this must be a rumor, right?

806
00:32:19,590 --> 00:32:20,550
Why do I

807
00:32:20,550 --> 00:32:21,950
have no judgment at all to these rumors?

808
00:32:21,950 --> 00:32:22,550
Besides,

809
00:32:22,550 --> 00:32:23,950
it's not really appropriate

810
00:32:23,950 --> 00:32:24,590
for teachers from the same school

811
00:32:24,590 --> 00:32:25,500
to date,

812
00:32:25,500 --> 00:32:26,500
right, Director?

813
00:32:27,390 --> 00:32:28,750
Alright, don't worry about

814
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:30,510
our teachers' personal matters.

815
00:32:30,510 --> 00:32:31,470
Okay, it's time.

816
00:32:31,710 --> 00:32:32,630
Teachers get back to class,

817
00:32:32,630 --> 00:32:34,090
and the parent heads home.

818
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:38,750
Well...

819
00:32:38,990 --> 00:32:40,550
Ms. Han, your stomach...

820
00:32:40,550 --> 00:32:41,430
You come back.

821
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:48,110
Well, you...

822
00:32:48,590 --> 00:32:49,550
You done eating, Director?

823
00:32:49,550 --> 00:32:50,190
Yes.

824
00:32:50,350 --> 00:32:51,350
How was the taste?

825
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:53,820
The soup was really good,

826
00:32:54,820 --> 00:32:56,050
but the meat was a bit too salty.

827
00:32:56,050 --> 00:32:57,310
I prefer things light.

828
00:32:59,430 --> 00:33:00,110
Light?

829
00:33:06,960 --> 00:33:08,200
Mom, I'm back.

830
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:09,100
You're back?

831
00:33:15,850 --> 00:33:18,100
Mom, Yang didn't come home?

832
00:33:18,890 --> 00:33:19,610
No.

833
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,170
He left right after the meeting.

834
00:33:21,170 --> 00:33:22,170
He didn't go home.

835
00:33:26,050 --> 00:33:27,130
Did you ask him

836
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:28,400
about the Walkman?

837
00:33:28,420 --> 00:33:29,480
Did he buy it or not?

838
00:33:29,810 --> 00:33:31,520
Ask him yourself when you see him.

839
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:32,870
Why should I ask about it for you?

840
00:33:32,870 --> 00:33:34,710
I didn't see him.

841
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,370
The food is in the pot.

842
00:33:39,590 --> 00:33:41,710
How about I heat it up for you now?

843
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:42,480
Mom.

844
00:33:44,470 --> 00:33:46,330
The color of the lipstick is good.

845
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:47,630
Isn't it too red?

846
00:33:47,630 --> 00:33:48,390
It's the lipstick

847
00:33:48,390 --> 00:33:49,190
you gave me.

848
00:33:49,210 --> 00:33:49,950
I'll go wipe it off.

849
00:33:49,950 --> 00:33:52,080
No, don't wipe it off. It looks nice.

850
00:33:52,530 --> 00:33:54,130
What, are you going dancing?

851
00:33:56,030 --> 00:33:57,850
Your aunties insisted that I go.

852
00:33:58,430 --> 00:33:58,950
And since

853
00:33:58,950 --> 00:33:59,990
Yang isn't home,

854
00:34:00,450 --> 00:34:02,380
I thought I'd go get some exercise.

855
00:34:02,670 --> 00:34:04,600
You should still go if he were home.

856
00:34:05,250 --> 00:34:06,800
Where's that fierce attitude of yours?

857
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,540
Sobering up now and chickening out, huh?

858
00:34:08,540 --> 00:34:10,040
How could  you say that to your mom?

859
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:10,610
Go.

860
00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:12,460
I'm backing you up. Go.

861
00:34:12,489 --> 00:34:13,310
How about I...

862
00:34:13,310 --> 00:34:14,150
-reheat the dinner for you?
-No need.

863
00:34:14,150 --> 00:34:15,580
Go. Go.

864
00:34:16,100 --> 00:34:16,650
Come on.

865
00:34:17,139 --> 00:34:18,400
I'm really going then.

866
00:34:18,750 --> 00:34:19,880
Let me grab my purse.

867
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:21,420
Enjoy dancing.

868
00:34:22,639 --> 00:34:23,949
Dancing is hard.

869
00:34:25,100 --> 00:34:26,429
It's really not too red?

870
00:34:26,429 --> 00:34:28,389
Not at all; it looks great.

871
00:34:28,790 --> 00:34:29,860
-Go.
-I'm off then.

872
00:34:30,580 --> 00:34:32,110
-Mom...
-Don't forget to eat when you're hungry.

873
00:34:32,110 --> 00:34:32,870
I know.

874
00:34:32,870 --> 00:34:34,060
Go. Hurry.

875
00:34:58,070 --> 00:34:58,660
Hello.

876
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:00,380
May I have this dance?

877
00:35:01,090 --> 00:35:01,950
Sorry.

878
00:35:01,950 --> 00:35:03,630
I don't... I don't know how to dance.

879
00:35:03,630 --> 00:35:05,350
I'm waiting for my friend.

880
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:05,930
She...

881
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:07,220
My friend is here.

882
00:35:07,220 --> 00:35:08,620
I'm sorry.

883
00:35:09,870 --> 00:35:11,380
What took you so long?

884
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,060
What's going on? Who was that?

885
00:35:13,140 --> 00:35:14,470
How would I know?

886
00:35:14,500 --> 00:35:15,880
He approached me and asked me to dance.

887
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,060
I'm so scared.

888
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:18,080
Then, dance with him.

889
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:19,760
Why are you scared?

890
00:35:19,790 --> 00:35:20,690
Could he eat you?

891
00:35:20,690 --> 00:35:21,720
I don't even know him.

892
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:23,600
How could I dance with him?

893
00:35:24,130 --> 00:35:26,190
Who says you have to know someone to dance with them?

894
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:27,480
Go dancing.

895
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:28,090
How?

896
00:35:28,130 --> 00:35:28,920
It's all hand-holding

897
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:29,910
and waist-grabbing.

898
00:35:29,910 --> 00:35:31,900
How can I dance with a stranger?

899
00:35:32,070 --> 00:35:32,930
How old are you?

900
00:35:32,940 --> 00:35:34,270
Why are you still so shy?

901
00:35:34,870 --> 00:35:36,370
Age has nothing to do with it.

902
00:35:36,370 --> 00:35:38,500
No matter how old we are, we have to mind our reputation.

903
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:39,380
Let me tell you.

904
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:40,230
I'm here to dance

905
00:35:40,230 --> 00:35:41,270
with you guys

906
00:35:41,270 --> 00:35:42,030
for exercise,

907
00:35:42,030 --> 00:35:42,910
not to dance

908
00:35:42,930 --> 00:35:44,320
with strange men.

909
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:47,480
That means you still got it.

910
00:35:47,660 --> 00:35:48,940
Oh, come on, Yu.

911
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:50,950
You're just teasing me again.

912
00:35:51,070 --> 00:35:53,000
Fine, then I'll ask you for a dance.

913
00:35:53,820 --> 00:35:55,360
Well, you'll have to stand up and ask me properly.

914
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:56,010
Okay.

915
00:35:57,140 --> 00:35:57,850
Come on.

916
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:03,290
I can never get that turn right.

917
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:24,490
Miaomiao, go to my home later.

918
00:36:24,490 --> 00:36:25,490
I have something.

919
00:36:25,750 --> 00:36:26,550
What is it?

920
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:27,600
Something.

921
00:36:32,160 --> 00:36:33,290
Where are you going?

922
00:36:33,830 --> 00:36:35,980
Do I have to report to you where I'm going?

923
00:36:35,980 --> 00:36:37,760
Who else would you report to if not me?

924
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:39,480
We have to

925
00:36:39,510 --> 00:36:40,830
keep each other updated in real-time, always.

926
00:36:40,830 --> 00:36:41,870
We don't need to do that.

927
00:36:41,870 --> 00:36:43,270
Let's enjoy our freedom.

928
00:36:44,910 --> 00:36:46,970
Freedom requires self-discipline!

929
00:36:48,590 --> 00:36:51,720
You've been using a lot of new words lately, haven't you?

930
00:36:51,910 --> 00:36:54,110
I've read a couple of philosophy books.

931
00:36:54,910 --> 00:36:55,970
Philosophy books?

932
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:03,190
[Heping Town]

933
00:37:11,860 --> 00:37:12,870
Jia Baoshan!

934
00:37:13,910 --> 00:37:14,840
Jia Baoshan!

935
00:37:15,220 --> 00:37:16,150
Coming! Coming!

936
00:37:16,550 --> 00:37:17,270
Are you done?

937
00:37:17,270 --> 00:37:18,310
Yes. Yes.

938
00:37:18,310 --> 00:37:20,230
Yu, here, take this.

939
00:37:20,870 --> 00:37:21,550
It's hot.

940
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:23,190
Let me... let me do it!

941
00:37:23,190 --> 00:37:24,720
What are you doing?

942
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:25,610
It's burning hot.

943
00:37:25,610 --> 00:37:26,560
Let me do it.

944
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:29,170
Yu, you...

945
00:37:30,150 --> 00:37:30,810
you really look like

946
00:37:30,810 --> 00:37:32,080
a mother-in-law now,

947
00:37:32,630 --> 00:37:35,030
liking to take care of your granddaughter.

948
00:37:35,430 --> 00:37:36,960
I never realized it before,

949
00:37:36,990 --> 00:37:37,960
but now that I'm older,

950
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:39,310
holding a baby...

951
00:37:39,990 --> 00:37:41,150
I suddenly understand

952
00:37:41,150 --> 00:37:42,140
why grandparents are always so fond of

953
00:37:42,140 --> 00:37:43,400
their grandchildren.

954
00:37:44,550 --> 00:37:45,500
It seems

955
00:37:45,500 --> 00:37:46,960
that you can only depend on me

956
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:49,160
having a little baby for you to care for.

957
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:50,560
What?

958
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:52,390
Did the chicken soup delivery go well today?

959
00:37:52,390 --> 00:37:53,850
Oh, it went very smoothly.

960
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:54,910
She has a great impression of me now

961
00:37:54,910 --> 00:37:56,100
in every way.

962
00:37:56,510 --> 00:37:57,750
I'm telling you, you have to be proactive and sincere

963
00:37:57,750 --> 00:37:59,030
when it comes to something like this.

964
00:37:59,030 --> 00:38:00,190
Whether a girl will date you or not

965
00:38:00,190 --> 00:38:01,470
depends on how much effort

966
00:38:01,470 --> 00:38:02,330
the guy puts in.

967
00:38:02,760 --> 00:38:04,070
Listen, be careful.

968
00:38:04,620 --> 00:38:05,350
Don't let it affect

969
00:38:05,350 --> 00:38:06,950
the kids' studies at school.

970
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:08,310
What are you talking about?

971
00:38:08,310 --> 00:38:09,150
I'm doing this

972
00:38:09,150 --> 00:38:10,390
for them to get better care.

973
00:38:10,390 --> 00:38:11,120
Understand?

974
00:38:11,950 --> 00:38:12,390
You should

975
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:13,720
take care of yourself first.

976
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:14,920
-Wait.
-Give it to me.

977
00:38:16,300 --> 00:38:18,230
Yu, have they caught Yuan Yong yet?

978
00:38:19,060 --> 00:38:19,830
Not yet.

979
00:38:20,750 --> 00:38:23,470
Evil deeds will eventually meet their punishment.

980
00:38:23,470 --> 00:38:25,750
Zi, time to drink your milk!

981
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:28,960
Yu!

982
00:38:29,310 --> 00:38:30,480
When I have kids with Ms. Han,

983
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:31,590
I'll leave them to you!

984
00:38:31,590 --> 00:38:32,510
In your dreams!

985
00:38:39,110 --> 00:38:39,910
This computer starts up

986
00:38:39,910 --> 00:38:41,710
way faster than those at school.

987
00:38:48,850 --> 00:38:50,910
Click on this, and you can get online.

988
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:53,600
You try it.

989
00:38:57,910 --> 00:38:58,710
Click this?

990
00:38:58,740 --> 00:38:59,270
Yes.

991
00:39:00,030 --> 00:39:01,590
I won't break it, will I?

992
00:39:02,990 --> 00:39:03,790
No.

993
00:39:04,270 --> 00:39:05,430
It's better

994
00:39:05,430 --> 00:39:05,990
than the school computers

995
00:39:05,990 --> 00:39:08,190
and connects directly to the internet.

996
00:39:11,390 --> 00:39:13,650
Your birthday gift is really expensive.

997
00:39:15,410 --> 00:39:17,340
Your gift to me is just as precious.

998
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:25,440
It's freezing.

999
00:39:26,470 --> 00:39:27,270
Uncle Chen.

1000
00:39:27,530 --> 00:39:28,730
Xiaowa, you're back?

1001
00:39:28,990 --> 00:39:29,710
Alright, you carry on.

1002
00:39:29,710 --> 00:39:30,350
Okay.

1003
00:39:32,010 --> 00:39:33,280
You missed me too, didn't you?

1004
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:33,910
Auntie.

1005
00:39:38,950 --> 00:39:39,910
Cheng Miaomiao?

1006
00:39:43,470 --> 00:39:44,590
Why are you here?

1007
00:39:46,350 --> 00:39:48,000
I saw that you weren't at school today.

1008
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:48,630
I was afraid that something might happen to you,

1009
00:39:48,630 --> 00:39:49,960
so I came to check on you.

1010
00:39:51,830 --> 00:39:53,090
Let's talk on the boat.

1011
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:01,750
Today, our old principal is sick,

1012
00:40:01,750 --> 00:40:02,910
so I went to visit him

1013
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:04,330
and couldn't make it to school.

1014
00:40:04,330 --> 00:40:05,990
Come on, to warm up your hands.

1015
00:40:08,380 --> 00:40:10,460
Did your village not have a school?

1016
00:40:11,230 --> 00:40:13,190
There used to be one, but...

1017
00:40:15,450 --> 00:40:16,180
not anymore.

1018
00:40:20,630 --> 00:40:21,990
It's getting cold today.

1019
00:40:21,990 --> 00:40:23,390
Why are you here?

1020
00:40:28,910 --> 00:40:30,170
Why is your face so red?

1021
00:40:30,330 --> 00:40:31,260
You have a fever?

1022
00:40:32,540 --> 00:40:33,430
No, I'm fine.

1023
00:40:35,010 --> 00:40:37,070
The wind was just too strong outside.

1024
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:42,710
Was it really that windy today?

1025
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:52,130
They're really not dating?

1026
00:40:53,080 --> 00:40:53,890
No.

1027
00:40:54,460 --> 00:40:57,060
They were just senior and junior schoolmates.

1028
00:40:57,620 --> 00:40:59,550
She's not even interested in such a handsome guy.

1029
00:40:59,550 --> 00:41:01,280
She has pretty high standards.

1030
00:41:02,230 --> 00:41:04,060
She's from Shanghai.

1031
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:05,640
Right.

1032
00:41:06,950 --> 00:41:07,950
Looks like...

1033
00:41:07,970 --> 00:41:09,830
I'll need to rethink my strategy.

1034
00:41:10,190 --> 00:41:12,590
I need to be more like people from Shanghai.

1035
00:41:13,430 --> 00:41:14,500
It's not easy.

1036
00:41:16,370 --> 00:41:17,170
Uncle.

1037
00:41:19,430 --> 00:41:20,660
How do you tell

1038
00:41:21,430 --> 00:41:22,270
if a girl

1039
00:41:22,270 --> 00:41:23,370
likes a boy?

1040
00:41:26,020 --> 00:41:28,180
If a girl

1041
00:41:28,340 --> 00:41:29,810
is constantly all over him

1042
00:41:30,220 --> 00:41:31,240
with no boundaries,

1043
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:33,190
then it's clear that she doesn't like him.

1044
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:34,350
But if she

1045
00:41:34,710 --> 00:41:36,540
deliberately avoids contact,

1046
00:41:38,070 --> 00:41:39,150
keeps her distance,

1047
00:41:39,150 --> 00:41:40,010
yet

1048
00:41:40,310 --> 00:41:40,950
still shows little acts of care

1049
00:41:40,950 --> 00:41:42,150
from time to time,

1050
00:41:42,470 --> 00:41:43,310
and gets a bit flustered

1051
00:41:43,310 --> 00:41:44,000
when people

1052
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:44,910
bring them up,

1053
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:46,990
then she definitely likes him.

1054
00:41:48,030 --> 00:41:49,360
Are you sure about that?

1055
00:41:49,790 --> 00:41:51,780
This is wisdom gained through my experience.

1056
00:41:51,780 --> 00:41:53,290
It's a proven truth.

1057
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:54,000
I am sure.

1058
00:41:57,630 --> 00:41:59,470
But in my case, Ms. Han

1059
00:41:59,830 --> 00:42:01,750
treats me so politely.

1060
00:42:02,460 --> 00:42:04,320
That doesn't look too good for me.

1061
00:42:06,150 --> 00:42:06,830
That's it.

1062
00:42:08,230 --> 00:42:09,030
It's all over.

1063
00:42:14,110 --> 00:42:15,150
Where are you going?

1064
00:42:15,150 --> 00:42:16,290
Aren't we going to the arcade?

1065
00:42:16,290 --> 00:42:18,090
No, I don't want to play anymore!

1066
00:42:22,310 --> 00:42:23,010
It's hard.

1067
00:42:28,940 --> 00:42:31,070
A person can be strong

1068
00:42:31,210 --> 00:42:32,640
with a firm heart

1069
00:42:32,670 --> 00:42:34,130
and unwavering strength,

1070
00:42:34,320 --> 00:42:35,520
yet no one

1071
00:42:35,550 --> 00:42:37,180
can remain strong forever.

1072
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,070
So, God has blessed us

1073
00:42:39,090 --> 00:42:41,220
with family, loved ones, and friends.

1074
00:42:41,700 --> 00:42:43,140
When we are happy,

1075
00:42:43,170 --> 00:42:44,370
they share in our joy.

1076
00:42:44,960 --> 00:42:46,440
When we're down,

1077
00:42:46,700 --> 00:42:48,050
they help us heal.

1078
00:42:48,810 --> 00:42:49,540
Don't worry.

1079
00:42:49,990 --> 00:42:52,110
Even if we fall, stumble,

1080
00:42:52,190 --> 00:42:53,320
or feel overwhelmed

1081
00:42:53,350 --> 00:42:54,630
by worry and hardship,

1082
00:42:55,450 --> 00:42:56,790
they will still stand before us

1083
00:42:56,790 --> 00:42:57,830
time and time again

1084
00:42:57,830 --> 00:42:59,290
and say, "Don't be afraid.

1085
00:42:59,350 --> 00:43:00,430
I'm here."

1086
00:43:01,550 --> 00:43:02,430
I'm grateful for every person

1087
00:43:02,430 --> 00:43:03,920
who has ever stood before me.
